beer_description: A medium-bodied brown ale with a rich malty character and a good dose of American Cascade hops.
Also called a 'Super Saison' because of the high alcohol content, this beer is brewed in the French style of Farmhoysr ales with imported malts and hops.

Slap Yer Mammy is a shocking Double IPA! Coming in at 10.5% ABV this huge ale is brewed with 7 of the highest quality malts and 9 varieties of hops! On our 125 minute boil we pack in 125 IBU's, making this one of the hoppiest beers ever brewed in the world. If that's not enough hops, then just wait! Unlike any of our other beers, we dry hop this one twice to pack in as much aroma as possible! A truly shocking Double IPA all you Hopophiles.

Named for the Comanche chief Potsanaquahip of the Penataka band, this fierce India Pale Ale remains true to the American brewing spirit, delivering long lasting hop flavor and character. Buffalo Hump led the Great Raid of 1840 in retaliation for the Texan settlers? betrayal under a white flag in San Antonio at the Council House Fight. This IPA represents the unrelenting spirit of our little brewery in north San Antonio, even when it becomes apparent we?ve brought knives to a gun fight. Inspired by bitter betrayal, this bitter brew will remind you to stay true to your sensibilities? and to your word!

A California-style IPA with a Belgian twist.

Stone Cali-Belgique IPA is a hop-forward transatlantic hybrid, the result of exposing Stone IPA to a Belgian culture. Literally. The addition of our Belgian yeast strain yields fascinating layers of flavor and aroma, lending new depth to the bright hoppiness of our flagship India pale ale. A gentle sweetness is more apparent, and you might even pick up hints of bubblegum.

Hops: Magnum, Perle & Centennial.

beer_description:
A chocolate stout made with Hershey?s and infused with whole vanilla beans and bacon. It has just a hint of vanilla and a slight smokiness 

This chocolate stout is made using Hershey?s Cocoa and is infused with whole Madagascar vanilla beans and Bespoke bacon, just in time for Winter. It has just a hint of vanilla and a slight smokiness from the locally procured, nitrate free bacon.

Our founder decided to experiment with chocolate & bacon in a beer after experiencing chocolate covered bacon for the first time. We start with an English Stout brewed with 50 pounds of Hershey?s Cocoa to create a brilliant chocolate stout. We then infuse it with over 100 Madagascar Vanilla Beans and bacon to get a touch of vanilla and smoke. The first few batches used a vegan friendly bacon, but that didn?t fit with our belief that anything we brew should be naturally sourced and not come from extracts or purees. Then we met the folks from Bespoke Bacon. Working with them we custom smoke a locally sourced pork belly and render out mostly all of the fat to give us that touch of smokiness without a single smoked malt being used. Doing so made some call us insane.

It just so happens that we brewed this beer in memory of a childhood friend of our founder who passed away in a tragic explosion in 1999. You can read out the accident here. Jay Insana was the son of the babysitter who helped raise our founder since he was a baby so the two grew up as brothers. After his death many of Jay?s close friend

All beer was once dark, but it was not until modern kilning of malts in the early 1800?s and the discovery of cold fermenting Lager strains in the 1840?s that allowed all the beautiful flavors of a Dunkel to come to life.  Dunkels, including Chuckanut?s, are typically a deep reddish-brown color, capped by an impressively sturdy tan head. As in all lagers, the flavors in Dunkel are produced directly by the ingredients; in this case some of the malts have been roasted, giving Dunkel toffee, chocolate, coffee, and even licorice notes. There is just enough bitterness to balance out the malt. Chuckanut Brewery?s Dunkel has won a total of seven prominent medals since 2009 (four Gold, two Silver, one Bronze) from the GABF, World Beer Cup 2010, WA Beer Awards and the NABA.
